{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013bRmcn6yrJGuTMZxzEHrXZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01BdRnUY1Sky1NFF7nswC8dc","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# RabbitMQ Cluster Upgrade & Configuration Migration Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-25  \n**Namespace:** karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-5f809e96-cluster-a  \n**Status:** DRAFT — review before executing in the change window\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State Snapshot\n\n### Cluster\n\n| Property | Value |\n|---|---|\n| RabbitMQ version | 3.12.14 (image: `rabbitmq:3.12-management`) |\n| Erlang/OTP | 25.3.2.15 (erts-13.2.2.11) |\n| Nodes | 3 disk nodes: rabbitmq-0, rabbitmq-1, rabbitmq-2 |\n| Cluster health | All running, no alarms, no network partitions |\n| Partition handling | `pause_minority` |\n| Queue master locator | `min-masters` (deprecated) |\n| Plugins | rabbitmq_prometheus, rabbitmq_management, rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s |\n| Support status | **Out of support** |\n\n### Virtual Hosts\n\n| VHost | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `/` | Default (empty, no queues) |\n| `/app` | Application messaging |\n| `/ops` | Operations messaging |\n\n### Users and Permissions\n\n| User | Tags | VHost | configure | write | read |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| admin | administrator | `/`, `/app`, `/ops` | `.*` | `.*` | `.*` |\n| app-user | management | `/app` | `.*` | `.*` | `.*` |\n| ops-user | management | `/ops` | `.*` | `.*` | `.*` |\n\n### Queues\n\n| VHost | Name | Type | Durable | x-queue-type arg | State |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `/app` | app-queue | classic | true | classic | running |\n| `/ops` | ops-queue | classic | true | classic | running |\n\n`app-queue` is bound to the default exchange with routing key `app-queue`.  \nNo custom exchanges. No queues in the default `/` vhost.\n\n### Policies\n\n| VHost | Name | Pattern | Apply-to | Definition | Priority |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `/app` | ha-all | `.*` | queues | `{\"ha-mode\":\"all\",\"ha-sync-mode\":\"automatic\"}` | 0 |\n\nNo policies are defined for `/ops` or `/`.\n\n### Feature Flags\n\nAll 17 currently available feature flags are **enabled** on all three nodes.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Issues Requiring Action Before or During Upgrade\n\n### 2a. Classic Mirrored Queues (BLOCKING for 4.0)\n\nThe `ha-all` policy in `/app` enables classic queue mirroring\n(`ha-mode: all`, `ha-sync-mode: automatic`). Classic mirrored queues are:\n\n- **Deprecated** since RabbitMQ 3.9\n- **Removed entirely** in RabbitMQ 4.0\n\n`app-queue` (and any future queues in `/app`) will **fail to start** on RabbitMQ 4.0\nwith this policy in place. This must be resolved before upgrading past 3.13.\n\nRecommended remediation: delete the `ha-all` policy and recreate `app-queue` as a\n**quorum queue** (which provides replication natively without a mirroring policy).\n\n`ops-queue` in `/ops` is a plain classic queue with no mirroring policy. It requires\nqueue-type migration to quorum before moving to 4.0 if HA for ops traffic is desired,\nor it can remain classic (non-replicated) if ops messaging tolerates node loss.\n\n### 2b. Deprecated `queue_master_locator` Setting\n\n`queue_master_locator = min-masters` is deprecated in 3.12 and removed in 4.0.\nThe equivalent in 4.0+ is `queue_leader_locator = balanced`. This setting must be\nremoved from `rabbitmq.conf` before upgrading to 4.0.\n\n### 2c. Version Support\n\nRabbitMQ 3.12 is out of community support. Security patches are no longer backported.\nUpgrade is recommended as soon as practicable.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Upgrade Path\n\nRabbitMQ requires upgrading through each minor/major version in sequence; skipping\nversions is not supported. The path from 3.12 to the current latest (4.1) is:\n\n```\n3.12.14  →  3.13.x  →  4.0.x  →  4.1.x\n```\n\nEach step is a rolling restart of the StatefulSet (update the image tag; Kubernetes\nrolls pods one at a time). The cluster remains operational during rolling restarts\nbecause `pause_minority` is set and the cluster has 3 nodes (quorum = 2).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Step-by-Step Change Plan\n\n### Step 1 — Pre-upgrade queue migration (still on 3.12)\n\n**Goal:** Eliminate classic mirrored queues before touching the image version.\n\n1. Pause all producers writing to `app-queue` (coordinate with the `app-producer`\n   Deployment) and drain the queue to zero messages.\n\n2. Delete the `ha-all` policy in `/app`:\n   ```\n   rabbitmqctl clear_policy -p /app ha-all\n   ```\n\n3. Delete the existing `app-queue` (it was declared with `x-queue-type=classic`\n   and cannot be converted in-place):\n   ```\n   rabbitmqctl delete_queue -p /app app-queue\n   ```\n\n4. Recreate `app-queue` as a quorum queue:\n   ```\n   rabbitmqctl declare_queue -p /app app-queue \\\n     --type quorum \\\n     --durable true\n   ```\n   Quorum queues replicate across all nodes by default (initial-quorum-size follows\n   the cluster size). No policy is required for replication.\n\n5. Optionally, add a quorum-queue-specific policy in `/app` for TTL or delivery\n   limits if required by the application SLA:\n   ```\n   rabbitmqctl set_policy -p /app qq-defaults \".*\" \\\n     '{\"delivery-limit\":20}' --apply-to quorum_queues\n   ```\n   (Omit if no additional controls are needed.)\n\n6. Assess `ops-queue` in `/ops`:\n   - If ops traffic requires HA: apply the same drain → delete → recreate-as-quorum\n     procedure for `ops-queue`.\n   - If ops traffic is low-criticality and node-loss tolerance is acceptable, `ops-queue`\n     may remain as a classic queue. Classic queues continue to function on 4.0 and 4.1\n     (only classic *mirrored* queues are removed).\n\n7. Resume producers and verify `app-queue` is receiving and delivering messages.\n\n### Step 2 — Update rabbitmq.conf before 4.0\n\nRemove the deprecated `queue_master_locator` line and replace it with the 4.0\nequivalent. In the ConfigMap or Secret that backs `rabbitmq.conf`, change:\n\n```\n# Remove this line:\nqueue_master_locator = min-masters\n\n# Add this line (effective from 3.12+, native in 4.0):\nqueue_leader_locator = balanced\n```\n\nApply the ConfigMap change and trigger a rolling restart of the StatefulSet to pick\nup the new configuration.\n\n### Step 3 — Upgrade 3.12 → 3.13 (rolling)\n\n1. Update the StatefulSet image from `rabbitmq:3.12-management` to\n   `rabbitmq:3.13-management` (or the specific patch, e.g. `3.13.7-management`).\n\n2. Apply the StatefulSet update; Kubernetes will rolling-restart pods one at a time.\n   Monitor each pod: wait for it to reach `Running/Ready` before the next rolls.\n\n3. After all three nodes are on 3.13, enable any new feature flags introduced in 3.13\n   (RabbitMQ will not enable them automatically):\n   ```\n   rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all\n   ```\n\n4. Verify cluster health:\n   ```\n   rabbitmqctl cluster_status\n   rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /app name type state\n   rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /ops name type state\n   ```\n\n### Step 4 — Upgrade 3.13 → 4.0 (rolling)\n\n1. Confirm Step 1 is complete — no classic mirrored queues exist in any vhost, and\n   no `ha-mode` policy is active.\n\n2. Update the StatefulSet image to `rabbitmq:4.0-management`.\n\n3. Rolling restart proceeds as in Step 3. Monitor closely: the Mnesia-to-Khepri\n   metadata store migration may occur on first startup of the 4.0 node (this is\n   automatic and irreversible).\n\n4. After all three nodes are on 4.0, enable all 4.0 feature flags:\n   ```\n   rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all\n   ```\n\n5. Verify cluster health, queues, and application connectivity.\n\n### Step 5 — Upgrade 4.0 → 4.1 (rolling)\n\n1. Update the StatefulSet image to `rabbitmq:4.1-management`.\n\n2. Rolling restart. Enable feature flags after all nodes upgrade:\n   ```\n   rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all\n   ```\n\n3. Final verification:\n   ```\n   rabbitmqctl status\n   rabbitmqctl cluster_status\n   rabbitmqctl list_vhosts\n   rabbitmqctl list_users\n   rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /app name type state messages\n   rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /ops name type state messages\n   rabbitmqctl list_policies -p /app\n   ```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Considerations\n\n| Step | Rollback feasibility |\n|---|---|\n| Step 1 (queue migration) | Producers must be paused; rollback = recreate classic queue and restore ha-all policy while still on 3.12. |\n| Step 2 (conf update) | Revert ConfigMap and rolling-restart. |\n| Step 3 (3.12→3.13) | Possible if feature flags have NOT been enabled (flag enablement is irreversible). Do not run `enable_feature_flag all` until the upgrade is confirmed. |\n| Step 4 (3.13→4.0) | **Not recommended after feature flags are enabled.** Treat 4.0 as a point of no return for the metadata store migration. |\n| Step 5 (4.0→4.1) | Same caution as Step 4. |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Risk Register\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|\n| `app-queue` message loss during drain | High | Pause producers; verify queue depth = 0 before delete |\n| ha-all policy on /app blocks 4.0 node startup | High | Step 1 must complete before Step 4 |\n| `queue_master_locator` config causes 4.0 node startup failure | Medium | Step 2 must complete before Step 4 |\n| Erlang version compatibility | Medium | `rabbitmq:4.x-management` ships a compatible Erlang; verify if using a custom image |\n| ops-queue on non-HA classic after migration | Low | Acceptable if ops traffic tolerates broker-node loss; document the decision |\n| Producer reconnect handling during rolling restart | Low | Verify app clients implement AMQP connection retry; quorum queues re-elect a new leader automatically |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Verification Checklist (post-upgrade)\n\n- [ ] All three nodes report the target version via `rabbitmqctl status`\n- [ ] `rabbitmqctl cluster_status` shows no partitions, all nodes running\n- [ ] `/app`, `/ops`, `/` vhosts present\n- [ ] `app-user` retains full permissions on `/app`; `ops-user` retains full permissions on `/ops`\n- [ ] `app-queue` exists as **quorum** type, state running, reachable by app-client\n- [ ] `ops-queue` exists, state running, reachable by ops-client\n- [ ] No `ha-mode` or `ha-sync-mode` policies remain\n- [ ] Prometheus metrics scraping active on port 15692\n- [ ] `rabbitmq_management`, `rabbitmq_prometheus`, `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s` plugins enabled\n- [ ] No alarms reported\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1257,"cache_read_input_tokens":37581,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1257},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"123f0d33-06aa-4216-98ab-776cddb64e3b","uuid":"e1e3bc56-e720-4375-921d-6637fd9230d9","request_id":"req_011CcQ5n4LSQWmfr2Xfv3Ywu"}
