{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01BVhb5CEQE3XzhEmKVUWfay","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01D8q5V1FA4Ef4Czih9HhrsV","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > /tmp/plan.md << 'PLANEOF'\n# RabbitMQ Cluster Upgrade & Configuration Migration Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-25  \n**Namespace:** karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-5f809e96-cluster-a  \n**Status:** DRAFT — review before executing in the change window\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State Snapshot\n\n### Cluster\n\n| Property | Value |\n|---|---|\n| RabbitMQ version | 3.12.14 (image: `rabbitmq:3.12-management`) |\n| Erlang/OTP | 25.3.2.15 (erts-13.2.2.11) |\n| Nodes | 3 disk nodes: rabbitmq-0, rabbitmq-1, rabbitmq-2 |\n| Cluster health | All running, no alarms, no network partitions |\n| Partition handling | `pause_minority` |\n| Queue master locator | `min-masters` (deprecated in 3.12, removed in 4.0) |\n| Plugins | rabbitmq_prometheus, rabbitmq_management, rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s |\n| Support status | **Out of support** |\n\n### Virtual Hosts\n\n| VHost | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `/` | Default (empty — no queues or policies) |\n| `/app` | Application messaging |\n| `/ops` | Operations messaging |\n\n### Users and Permissions\n\n| User | Tags | VHost | configure | write | read |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| admin | administrator | `/`, `/app`, `/ops` | `.*` | `.*` | `.*` |\n| app-user | management | `/app` | `.*` | `.*` | `.*` |\n| ops-user | management | `/ops` | `.*` | `.*` | `.*` |\n\n### Queues\n\n| VHost | Name | Type | Durable | x-queue-type argument | State |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `/app` | app-queue | classic | true | classic | running |\n| `/ops` | ops-queue | classic | true | classic | running |\n\n`app-queue` is bound to the default exchange via routing key `app-queue`.  \nNo custom exchanges. No queues in the default `/` vhost.\n\n### Policies\n\n| VHost | Name | Pattern | Apply-to | Definition | Priority |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `/app` | ha-all | `.*` | queues | `{\"ha-mode\":\"all\",\"ha-sync-mode\":\"automatic\"}` | 0 |\n\nNo policies are defined for `/ops` or `/`.\n\n### Feature Flags\n\nAll 17 currently available feature flags are **enabled** on all three nodes\n(classic_mirrored_queue_version, quorum_queue, stream_queue, feature_flags_v2,\nand 13 others).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Issues Requiring Action Before or During Upgrade\n\n### 2a. Classic Mirrored Queues — BLOCKING for 4.0\n\nThe `ha-all` policy in `/app` enables classic queue mirroring\n(`ha-mode: all`, `ha-sync-mode: automatic`). Classic mirrored queues are:\n\n- Deprecated since RabbitMQ 3.9\n- **Removed entirely in RabbitMQ 4.0**\n\n`app-queue` (and any future queues matching `.*` in `/app`) will **fail to start**\non 4.0 nodes while this policy is active. It must be removed and the queue\nmigrated to a quorum queue before upgrading past 3.13.\n\n`ops-queue` in `/ops` has no mirroring policy and is not blocked, but it remains\na non-replicated classic queue.\n\n### 2b. Deprecated `queue_master_locator` Setting\n\n`queue_master_locator = min-masters` in `rabbitmq.conf` is deprecated in 3.12 and\nremoved in 4.0. The replacement setting is `queue_leader_locator = balanced`.\nThis must be updated in the ConfigMap backing `rabbitmq.conf` before upgrading to 4.0.\n\n### 2c. Version Support Gap\n\nRabbitMQ 3.12 reached end-of-community-support in December 2024. Security patches\nare no longer backported. Upgrading is recommended as soon as practicable.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Upgrade Path\n\nRabbitMQ requires upgrading through each minor/major version in sequence; jumping\nversions is unsupported. The path from 3.12 to the current latest stable (4.1) is:\n\n```\n3.12.14  →  3.13.x  →  4.0.x  →  4.1.x\n```\n\nEach step is a rolling restart of the StatefulSet (update the container image tag).\nWith `pause_minority` and 3 nodes (quorum = 2), the cluster remains available while\none pod restarts at a time.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Step-by-Step Change Plan\n\n### Step 1 — Pre-upgrade: migrate app-queue to quorum (on 3.12)\n\n**Prerequisite:** complete this step while the cluster is still running 3.12, before\nany image upgrade.\n\n1. Coordinate with the `app-producer` Deployment to pause message publishing to\n   `app-queue`. Wait for the queue depth to reach zero (drain in-flight messages).\n\n2. Delete the `ha-all` mirroring policy:\n   ```sh\n   rabbitmqctl clear_policy -p /app ha-all\n   ```\n\n3. Delete `app-queue` (cannot convert queue type in place):\n   ```sh\n   rabbitmqctl delete_queue -p /app app-queue\n   ```\n\n4. Recreate `app-queue` as a quorum queue:\n   ```sh\n   rabbitmqctl declare_queue -p /app app-queue \\\n     --type quorum --durable true\n   ```\n   Quorum queues replicate across nodes by default (initial-quorum-size defaults to\n   the cluster's `min(3, node_count)`). No additional policy is required for HA.\n\n5. Optionally set a quorum-queue policy for delivery-limit or TTL if required by\n   application SLAs (this is additive and non-blocking):\n   ```sh\n   rabbitmqctl set_policy -p /app qq-defaults \".*\" \\\n     '{\"delivery-limit\":20}' --apply-to quorum_queues\n   ```\n\n6. Decide on `ops-queue` in `/ops`: it currently has no mirroring policy and is not\n   blocked by the 4.0 upgrade. However, if `/ops` traffic requires HA, apply the\n   same drain → delete → recreate-as-quorum procedure. If ops messaging tolerates\n   node loss, `ops-queue` may remain a classic queue (plain classic queues — without\n   mirroring — continue to work on 4.0 and 4.1).\n\n7. Resume producers and verify `app-queue` is receiving and delivering messages\n   before proceeding to Step 2.\n\n### Step 2 — Update rabbitmq.conf before upgrading to 4.0\n\nIn the ConfigMap or Secret backing `rabbitmq.conf`, make the following change:\n\n```diff\n-queue_master_locator = min-masters\n+queue_leader_locator = balanced\n```\n\nApply the ConfigMap update and perform a rolling restart of the StatefulSet so\nall three nodes pick up the new configuration while still on 3.12.\n\n### Step 3 — Upgrade 3.12 → 3.13 (rolling)\n\n1. Update the StatefulSet container image to `rabbitmq:3.13-management` (or a\n   specific patch release, e.g. `rabbitmq:3.13.7-management`).\n\n2. Apply the StatefulSet change. Kubernetes will restart pods one at a time.\n   Wait for each pod to reach `Running/Ready` before the next rolls.\n\n3. After all three nodes are on 3.13, enable any new feature flags introduced\n   in 3.13 (feature flags are never auto-enabled):\n   ```sh\n   rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all\n   ```\n\n4. Verify:\n   ```sh\n   rabbitmqctl cluster_status\n   rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /app name type state\n   rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /ops name type state\n   ```\n\n### Step 4 — Upgrade 3.13 → 4.0 (rolling)\n\n**Prerequisite:** Steps 1 and 2 must be complete. Confirm no `ha-mode` policies\nexist in any vhost before proceeding.\n\n1. Update the StatefulSet image to `rabbitmq:4.0-management`.\n\n2. Rolling restart. Monitor each pod's logs during startup; 4.0 performs an\n   automatic Mnesia→Khepri metadata-store migration on first boot — this is\n   expected, one-way, and may add 30–60 s to the first pod's startup time.\n\n3. After all nodes are on 4.0, enable 4.0 feature flags:\n   ```sh\n   rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all\n   ```\n\n4. Verify cluster status, queue health, and application connectivity before\n   proceeding to Step 5.\n\n### Step 5 — Upgrade 4.0 → 4.1 (rolling)\n\n1. Update the StatefulSet image to `rabbitmq:4.1-management`.\n\n2. Rolling restart. Enable feature flags after all nodes are on 4.1:\n   ```sh\n   rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all\n   ```\n\n3. Final verification (see Section 7).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Considerations\n\n| Step | Rollback feasibility |\n|---|---|\n| Step 1 (queue migration) | Before any image change: recreate classic `app-queue`, reapply `ha-all` policy while still on 3.12. Requires re-draining the quorum queue. |\n| Step 2 (conf update) | Revert ConfigMap and rolling-restart on 3.12. |\n| Step 3 (3.12→3.13) | Possible **before** running `enable_feature_flag all`. Feature-flag enablement is irreversible; downgrade after enablement is unsupported. |\n| Step 4 (3.13→4.0) | **Not recommended** after 4.0 boots: the Mnesia→Khepri migration is one-way. Treat 4.0 as a point of no return. |\n| Step 5 (4.0→4.1) | Same caution as Step 4. |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Risk Register\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|\n| `app-queue` message loss during drain/delete | High | Pause producers; confirm queue depth = 0 before `delete_queue` |\n| `ha-all` policy still active when 4.0 node boots | High | Step 1 and 3 must complete before Step 4 |\n| `queue_master_locator` in conf blocks 4.0 node startup | Medium | Step 2 must complete before Step 4 |\n| Mnesia→Khepri migration failure on first 4.0 boot | Medium | Take a snapshot/backup of PVCs before Step 4; test in staging first |\n| ops-queue loses messages if its node dies (no mirroring) | Low–Medium | Decide during Step 1 whether to migrate ops-queue to quorum |\n| Erlang compatibility if using a non-official image | Low | `rabbitmq:4.x-management` bundles a compatible Erlang; verify if using a custom or pinned image |\n| App clients not handling leader re-election during restart | Low | Confirm AMQP client connection retry is implemented; quorum queues elect a new leader automatically |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Post-Upgrade Verification Checklist\n\n- [ ] All three nodes report the target version via `rabbitmqctl status`\n- [ ] `rabbitmqctl cluster_status` shows all nodes running, no partitions, no alarms\n- [ ] VHosts `/`, `/app`, `/ops` are present\n- [ ] `admin` user holds administrator tag; `app-user` and `ops-user` hold management tag\n- [ ] `app-user` has full (`.*`) permissions on `/app`; `ops-user` on `/ops`; `admin` on all three\n- [ ] `app-queue` exists in `/app` as type **quorum**, state running\n- [ ] `ops-queue` exists in `/ops`, state running\n- [ ] No `ha-mode` or `ha-sync-mode` entries in any active policy\n- [ ] Prometheus scraping active on port 15692 (check `prometheus-7b67994846-kmsr2` pod)\n- [ ] Plugins `rabbitmq_management`, `rabbitmq_prometheus`, `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s` enabled\n- [ ] No alarms reported (`rabbitmqctl list_alarms`)\n- [ ] `app-producer` and `app-client` are publishing/consuming successfully end-to-end\nPLANEOF\necho \"exit $?\"","description":"Write migration plan to /tmp/plan.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4264,"cache_read_input_tokens":38838,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4264},"output_tokens":43,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"123f0d33-06aa-4216-98ab-776cddb64e3b","uuid":"2729acac-9d11-41ac-a9d5-3a5462f14173","request_id":"req_011CcQ5s42Drpjzvt68pFjhQ"}
